    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-04-27T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-04-27T02:00:00-05:00" n="531"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d531">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/11907: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1"
                            type="from">Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary
                            of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-04-27T15:00:00+08:00"
                            >April 27, 1932—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 27—5:19 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your 155, April 25, 9 p.m.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>The British Minister has instructed his Consul at Amoy that it would be
                        desirable to defend Kulangsu provided all naval commanders agreed and that
                        foreigners should be evacuated only if absolutely <pb facs="0602" n="504"
                            xml:id="pg_504"/> necessary. He feels that an intimation that the
                        Settlement would be defended may prevent attack.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>In view of Amoy’s April 25, 6 p.m., and April 26, 7 [<hi rend="italic"
                            >10?</hi>] p.m.,<note n="49" xml:id="d531fn49">Latter not
                            printed.</note> I shall not for the present issue definite
                        instructions.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>With regard to paragraph 2 of the Department’s 155, I feel that
                        complications which might arise from close cooperation with the Japanese in
                        defending Kulangsu at this time would perhaps outweigh purely strategical
                        considerations but I shall keep in touch with my British colleague and bear
                        in mind Department’s suggestion.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
